quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  106,1,"(It is a great Grace from Allâh) for the protection of the Quraish,",""
  106,2,"(And with all those Allâh’s Grace and Protections, We cause) the (Quraish) caravans to set forth safe in winter (to the south) and in summer (to the north without any fear),",""
  106,3,"So let them worship (Allâh) the Lord of this House (the Ka‘bah in Makkah),",""
  106,4,"(He) Who has fed them against hunger, and has made them safe from fear.",""
  107,1,"Have you seen him who denies the Recompense?",""
  107,2,"That is he who repulses the orphan (harshly),<sup>1</sup>","[1] (V.107:2) Narrated Sahl bin Sa‘d رضي الله عنهما : The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, ""I and the person who looks after an orphan and provides for him, will be in Paradise like this,"" putting his index and middle fingers together. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.8, Hadith No.34)."
  107,3,"And urges not on the feeding of Al-Miskîn (the poor),<sup>2</sup>","[2] (V.107:3) Narrated Abû Hurairah رضي الله عنه: The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, ""The one who looks after a widow or a poor person is like a Mujâhid (fighter) who fights for Allâh’s Cause, or like him who performs prayers all the night and fasts all the day."" (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.7, Hadith No.265)."
  107,4,"So woe unto those performers of Salât (prayers) (hypocrites),",""
  107,5,"Those who delay their Salât (prayer from their stated fixed times).",""
  107,6,"Those who do good deeds only to be seen (of men),",""
  107,7,"And prevent Al-Mâ‘ûn (small kindnesses like salt, sugar, water).",""
  108,1,"Verily, We have granted you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) Al-Kauthar (a river in Paradise).<sup>1</sup>","[1] (V.108:1) Narrated Anas رضي الله عنه: When the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم was made to ascend to the heavens. He صلى الله عليه وسلم said (after his return), ""I came upon a river (in Paradise) the banks of which were made of tents of hollow pearls. I asked Jibrîl (Gabriel), ‘What is this (river)?’ He replied, ‘This is the Kauthar’ "" (Sahih Al-Bukhâri, Vol.6, Hadîth No. 488)."
  108,2,"Therefore turn in prayer to your Lord and sacrifice (to Him only).",""
  108,3,"For he who hates you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم), he will be cut off (from posterity and every good thing in this world and in the Hereafter).<sup>2</sup>","[2] (V.108:3) Narrated Anas رضي الله عنه : The Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم said, ""None of you will have Faith till he loves me more than his father, his children and all mankind. (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.1, Hadith No.14)."
